  <front>
   <head>On WIT.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">TRUE wit is like the brilliant stone</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Dug from the Indian mine;</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Which boasts two various powers in one</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">To cut as well as shine,</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Genius, like that, if polish'd right,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">With the same gifts abounds;</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Appears at once both keen and bright,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And sparkles while it wounds.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
